I

IEvent - Interface in pec
Interface representing the contract to be used by classes of other packages to interact with a general event.
IIndividual - Interface in simulation
IIndividual interface complements this package with methods to act over individuals of a population development simulation, all the action of the simulation is centered in these methods, these are the behaviors that define the development of the simulation and ultimately the result
IMap - Interface in map
IMap interface is used to get general properties from a certain map
IMap_node - Interface in map
IMap_node interface gives methods needed to navigate through the simulation
Individual - Class in simulation
Individual is the class that implements IIndividual interface, it overrides the interface methods stating how the actions should be delivered, each new individual is an instance of this class described by: cost - Accumulated cost by traveling along the map, since each edge has a cost of transversing associated; length - Number of edges traveled by this individual; death - Boolean value that indicates if the individual is already death or not path - Map nodes transversed by this individual hs - HashSet used to store the Map nodes already transversed by this individual in this way the program could know efficiently if a node is already on the list or not, saving time compared to searching all the list sim - simulation associated with this individual
Individual(LinkedList<IMap_node>, HashSet<IMap_node>, Simulation, int) - Constructor for class simulation.Individual
This class Individual constructor is generally used to generate a new Individual from a parent
Individual(IMap_node, Simulation) - Constructor for class simulation.Individual
This class Individual constructor is used to generate a new individual, with only one node in its path, its generally used to populate the simulation in the beginning
IPEC - Interface in pec
Contract for the general methods of a PEC class
ISimulation - Interface in simulation
ISimulation interface is used for population development simulations and has the methods used to print reports based on the simulation actual state and to get simulation general parameters that define the behavior of the simulation
